title: Which drivers are still in the Chase at Talladega? | AL.com
text:
The 2015 Chase for the NASCAR Sprint Cup championship continues at Talladega, as 12 drivers remain in the competition.
Talladega is the last of the Contender Round races, and the Chase changes to the Eliminator Round after this weekend. Just eight drivers can advance into the Eliminator Round.
The 12 remaining drivers in the Chase at Dega, in order of current standings are: Joey Logano, Denny Hamlin, Kurt Busch, Carl Edwards, Kevin Harvick, Jeff Gordon, Brad Keselowski, Martin Truex Jr., Kyle Busch, Ryan Newman, Dale Earnhardt Jr. and Matt Kenseth.
That means there's plenty of drama for Talladega's CampingWorld.com 500 on Sunday afternoon. (Dale Jr., for example, likely must win the race to advance.)
